<p>I need to use VB .Net to feed an XML document into a CrystalReports template, producing a PDF document.</p>  <p>Here is my current working:</p>  <pre><code>    Dim xml As String = "C:\XML\input.xml"     Dim rpt As ReportDocument = New ReportDocument()     Dim ds As DataSet = New DataSet()      rpt.Load("C:\Crystal\template.rpt")     ds.ReadXml(xmlfile)     rpt.SetDataSource(ds)     Dim filename As String = "C:\Output\output.pdf"     rpt.ExportToDisk(ExportFormatType.PortableDocFormat, filename) </code></pre>  <p>This throws an error on the final line about not finding the filepath. Curiously, if I comment out <code>rpt.SetDataSource(ds)</code> it executes without errors - however as it just generates a PDF with the static data specified in the Crystal document.</p>